.TH VIRT-CHECK "1" "December 2025" "virt-check 202208181627-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
virt-check \- Check if processor supports virtualization
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B virt-check
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B virt-check
is a script for checking if the processor supports hardware virtualization. It detects Intel VT-x or AMD-V support and reports whether virtualization extensions are available and enabled.
.PP
The script is useful for verifying virtualization capability before installing hypervisors.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B virt-check
Check current system virtualization support
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/virt-check/settings.conf
User configuration file for virt-check preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Virtualization supported
.TP
.B 1
Virtualization not supported or not enabled
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
Checks Intel VT-x and AMD-V
.IP \(bu 2
Reads /proc/cpuinfo for flags
.IP \(bu 2
May require BIOS/UEFI settings
